[
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Ellicott's Commentary for English Readers",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(3) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Therefore came all the elders of Israel.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—The assembly of elders, the Senate of Israel, make a contract with David concerning his prerogative and the rights of his people, thus formally determining “the manner of the kingdom.” (Comp. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1Samuel 8:9",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "seq.,",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1Samuel 10:25",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".) Representative institutions appear to have been the rule in the best period of Israel’s national existence. The elders or hereditary heads of the tribal subdivisions met in council to discuss and settle matters of national concern. (Comp. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1Chronicles 12:23",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".)",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Before the Lord.—In the presence of the high priest, and perhaps before the ark; comp. Exodus 21:6; 1Samuel 2:25, where the priestly nudge is called God, as representing the authority of the Divine judge (Exodus 22:28).",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "Before the Lord.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—In the presence of the high priest, and perhaps before the ark; comp. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Exodus 21:6",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1Samuel 2:25",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", where the priestly nudge is called God, as representing the authority of the Divine judge (",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Exodus 22:28",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ").",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "According to the word of the Lord by Samuel.—A reflection added by the chronicler, and based upon the facts related in 1Samuel 15:28; 1Samuel 16:1-13.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "According to the word of the Lord by Samuel.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—A reflection added by the chronicler, and based upon the facts related in ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1Samuel 15:28",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1Samuel 16:1-13",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ".",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
